gomodel:SYNGO_1703  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors treat rat brain synaptosomes with GTPgammaS preventing the budding of clathrin coated vesicles. By EM (Figures 2c-j) dynamin is seen to coat the necks of the clathrin-coated pits. In figure 2a/b the author use conventional light microscopy to show dynamin 1 in presynaptic terminals.\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- I have removed the 'extrinsic component of ...' element of the selected term because the mode of membrane interaction was not addressed in the presented data.. Experimental description: Legend to figure 1, \"Membrane fractions....were prepared from rat brain homogenates\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1703" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

